the poems, and they were wonderful.

00:06:39.360 --> 00:06:40.740
They were really good.

00:06:40.740 --> 00:06:46.300 position:56%
But at the same time, I had received
a manuscript of another poet,

00:06:46.300 --> 00:06:51.390
Rira Abbasi, an Iranian poet, and
Jesse Lee's poems, a lot of them,

00:06:51.390 --> 00:06:54.590
the ones from Circe Maia
had already been published,

00:06:54.590 --> 00:06:57.830
and none of the poems from this
Rira Abbasi, this Iranian poet,

00:06:57.830 --> 00:07:01.080
had ever been published
in English before,

00:07:01.080 --> 00:07:02.590
and Jesse Lee had the
book coming out.

00:07:02.590 --> 00:07:06.300
And so thinking about Poet Lore's,
you know, emphasis on discovery

00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:10.440
and bringing new voices to people,
I made a really hard decision,

00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:13.580
and it was really hard to write
the email, but I said to Jesse Lee,

00:07:13.580 --> 00:07:15.420
"I love these poems, but
you've got so many out

00:07:15.420 --> 00:07:17.310
