done exactly the same thing."

00:07:24.460 --> 00:07:29.190
And I think I told our managing
editor, Jen, about that,

00:07:29.190 --> 00:07:31.940
and she said, "That was,
like, the perfect response."

00:07:31.940 --> 00:07:36.920
And I said, "Yes," and not only
because it was gracious and kind,

00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:40.510
but also I think because it
embodies the spirit of translation,

00:07:40.510 --> 00:07:44.410
which is you are putting
forth somebody else's work.

00:07:44.410 --> 00:07:47.810
You're expanding the circle so
that more voices can come in.

00:07:47.810 --> 00:07:51.350
Not just, you know,
promoting your own voice,

00:07:51.350 --> 00:07:53.300
and that really made
an impression on me.

00:07:53.300 --> 00:07:55.160
And then this year,
as I was looking,

00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:58.200 position:56%
I remember Jesse Lee had said,
"Well, I'll be doing other writers."

00:07:58.200 --> 00:08:01.430
So I sent an email
out, and lucky for me,

00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:05.560
not only is Jesse Lee gracious and
generous, but she's hardworking

00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:06.860
and prolific and talented.

00:08:06.860 --> 00:08:11.890
