00:10:19.100 --> 00:10:22.240
But she doesn't have a book in
English translated, and this,

00:10:22.240 --> 00:10:25.500 position:56%
these poems are from her most famous
book, Poemas de Amor, Love Poems.

00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:30.050
She was born in 1920
and she died in 2009

00:10:30.050 --> 00:10:33.700
and lived her whole life
in Montevideo, Uruguay.

00:10:33.700 --> 00:10:38.600
But she, the poems, Poemas de Amor,
are a really fascinating story.

00:10:38.600 --> 00:10:42.040
Idea Vilarino was part of what's
called the Generation of 45

00:10:42.040 --> 00:10:45.070
in Uruguay, which included
Mario Benedetti,

00:10:45.070 --> 00:10:47.570
and is sort of an ex
officio Argentine member,

00:10:47.570 --> 00:10:50.500
Borges, Jorge Luis Borges.

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:55.630 position:56%
And she was, fell madly in love with
one of the most important members

00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:58.780
of the group, the Cervantes
Prize winning novelist,

00:10:58.780 --> 00:11:02.170
Juan Carlos Onetti, who was
ten years older than she was.

00:11:02.170 --> 00:11:06.280 position:56%
And I wish I could show you pictures
because Idea Vilarino looks like,

00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:09.920
you know, looks like
a young Lauren Bacall.

00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:11.220
She's gorgeous.

00:11:11.220 --> 00:11:12.520
And I hate to say it,
but Onetti looks

00:11:12.520 --> 00:11:13.900
like a frog wearing big glasses.

00:11:13.900 --> 00:11:18.410
And so their love affair
is very famous in Uruguay

00:11:18.410 --> 00:11:21.880
and in Latin America, sort of
the Frida Kahlo, Diego Rivera;

00:11:21.880 --> 00:11:23.700
Sylvia Plath, Ted Hughes; you know.

00:11:23.700 --> 00:11:25.000
I don't know.

00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:26.520
Lauren Bacall, Humphrey
Bogart romance.

00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:28.510
He dedicated a book to her.

00:11:28.510 --> 00:11:32.050
She wrote these poems to him, so
every amor, every love in the poem,

00:11:32.050 --> 00:11:34.200
in the book, is addressed to him.

00:11:34.200 --> 00:11:37.130
But it has a story
almost beyond their love.

